  "summary": "Moderate: kernel-rt security update",
  "details": "The kernel-rt packages provide the Real Time Linux Kernel, which enables fine-tuning for systems with extremely high determinism requirements.  \n\nSecurity Fix(es):  \n\n  * kernel: RDMA/iwcm: Fix use-after-free of work objects after cm_id destruction (CVE-2025-38211)\n  * kernel: tipc: Fix use-after-free in tipc_conn_close() (CVE-2025-38464)\n\n\nFor more details about the security issue(s), including the impact, a CVSS score, acknowledgments, and other related information, refer to the CVE page(s) listed in the References section.\n",
